1. Requirements
  a) Appium.app
  b) Terminal
  c) Xcode  
  d) safari develop simulator inspector
  e) bundler

2. Steps
  a)Terminal create directory
   mkdir practice1
   cd practice1
   mkdir ios_safari
   cd ios_safari
  b)setup the gemfiles
   appium_lib
   bundle init
   open -a TextEdit Gemfile 
   cat Gemfile
   bundle install
 3.code
   touch simple.rb
   open -a TextEdit simple.rb

   ----------------------
   require 'rubygems'
   require 'appium_lib'


   desired_caps = {
  caps: {
  platformName: 'iOS',
  platformVersion: '9.3',
  deviceName: 'Iphone 5s',
  browserName:  'Safari',
	}
  }

 #Standard Selenium driver without any Appium methods.

@appium_driver = Appium::Driver.new(desired_caps)  
@selenium_driver = @appium_driver.start_driver

# Now promote appium methods to class instance methods.  More information at http://www.rubydoc.#info/github/appium/ruby_lib/Appium.promote_appium_methods

Appium.promote_appium_methods Object

@selenium_driver.get("http://www.google.com/")

